In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims May 19 through May 25, 2012, as National Safe Boating Week. The article emphasizes the importance of safe boating practices and encourages Americans to take basic safety precautions while on the water. These precautions include taking a boating safety course, performing a vessel safety check, filing a float plan, assessing weather conditions, wearing a life jacket at all times, and avoiding alcohol consumption while operating a boat. The United States Coast Guard collaborates with organizations and governments to prevent accidents and deaths related to unsafe recreational boating. The proclamation recognizes the significance of safe boating practices and highlights the joint resolution approved by Congress in 1958, which authorizes and requests the President to proclaim the 7-day period prior to Memorial Day weekend as National Safe Boating Week.